ENTRY            D0588   20260410   20260528   20260528       D152
SUBENT        D0588001   20260410   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                 13         32
TITLE      Production possibility of 186Re via the
            192Os(p,alpha+3n)186Re nuclear reaction
AUTHOR     (F.Szelecsenyi, G.F.Steyn, Z.Kovacs, K.Aardaneh,
           C.Vermeulen, T.N.Van Der Walt)
INSTITUTE  (3HUNDEB,3SAFITH)
           (3SAFSAF) Cape Peninsula Univ. of Technology, Bellville
REFERENCE  (J,JRN,282,261,2009)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3SAFITH) cyclotron of iThemba LABS.
SAMPLE     The enriched 192Os (99%) targets were prepared via
            electro-deposition onto 50 mu-m thick Cu foils. The
            thickness of the deposited layers varied between 2.94
            and 6.78 mg/cm2. The diameter of the osmium samples
            was 10 mm. One stack containing 15 pieces of 192Os
            foils together with thick Al degraders.
            The Cu backings and the Al degraders serve also as
            monitors
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
METHOD     (STTA,ACTIV,BCINT,CHSEP) The current measurement was
            done using a Faraday-cup
MONITOR    (29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-65,,SIG)
           (13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-22,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (,F.Tarkanyi+,R,IAEA-TECDOC-1211,49,2001)
ANALYSIS   The cross-sections were calculated using the
            activation equation.
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry approved by Dr. F.Szelecsenyi
           (TABLE,,F.Szelecsenyi+,J,JRN,282,261,2009) Table 1
HISTORY    (20091221C) SD
           (20190821A) SD: REACTION code updated according to new
           EXFOR rules in Subent 003.
           ERR-ANALYS moved to Subent 002.
           (20260410A) VT. Entry revised. DECAY-DATA moved to
            002. STATUS updated
ENDBIB              32
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           35
SUBENT        D0588002   20260410   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                  4         15
REACTION   (76-OS-192(P,X)75-RE-186-G,,SIG)
DECAY-DATA (75-RE-186-G,3.7183D,DG,137.157,0.0942)
ERR-ANALYS (EN-ERR) The energy uncertainty was estimated from the
            primary beam energy and target thickness, including
            energy straggling.
           (DATA-ERR) For estimation of the uncertainties of the
            cross-sections, the linearly contributing processes
            were taken into account with equal sensitivities.
           The errors of nonlinear parameters (time, etc.) were
            not considered but their contribution is negligible
            compared to the linear parameters.
           The typical cross-section uncertainty was around +/-16%
HISTORY    (20190821U) SD: ERR-ANALYS added from Subent 001.
           (20260410A) VT. RAECTION: -G in SF4 added; DECAY-DATA
            added from 001.
